Heat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 3cm sized chunks. Coarsely grate the @carrot{1} (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large deep #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Add the onion, carrot and pepper and continue to cook until the veggies are slightly softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1%tsp} (add less if you don't like heat!) and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @chopped tomatoes with basil{1%400g can}, @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water{150%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir well to dissolve the stock pot and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{10-12%minutes}. While the sauce simmers, add the @penne pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain well and mix with the Mexican beef. Transfer to a #baking dish{}, sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs and bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown on top, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Leave the pasta bake to stand for a couple of minutes then divide between plates and enjoy!

> This Beef Pasta Bake with a Cheesy Crumb is bursting full of flavours and make the perfect dinner night option.